    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's pretty good. can you make it sound just a little bit warmer though? like, we really liked this person and i'd love to keep them in our talent pool for next time. maybe add something about how we'll keep their resume on hand specifically because of those system design skills?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is a warmer version, focusing on keeping the door open for future contact. It sounds more enthusiastic about their potential, even if they weren't the right fit *this* time.\n\n***\n\n**Subject: Update on the Senior Developer Role at [Company Name]**\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you again for investing your time and energy into the final rounds for the Senior Developer position. We were genuinely excited about your candidacy; your grasp of system design was truly impressive, and we felt you connected so well with our team's culture. While we ultimately selected a candidate with more direct experience in our specific cloud stack for this immediate opening, please know this was an incredibly close decision.\n\nWe were so impressed by your strengths that we would absolutely love to keep your profile active in our talent pool. Your system design capabilities are exactly the kind of talent we look for, and we hope to connect with you again when a role that better aligns with your expertise opens up.\n\nWe wish you the absolute best in your next steps.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n\n***\n\n*This version feels much more like a genuine invitation to stay in touch, which is crucial for building a good talent pipeline.*",
      "source": "target",
